Inspection Dates: Oct 20 Oct 21 Oct 27 Oct 29 Oct 30 Nov 11 Nov 14 Nov 22
Particulars of distribution of spawning: Chum only spawn below log jam at bottom of section 1. Coho throughout, much intertidal spawning.
COMMENTS ON CONDITIONS AFFECTING THIS ST: (20a) Predator counts by date and predator type: Heavy bear predation, especially lower section 1 and estuary. (5) General Comments on Escapement Estimation: Section counts done so that AVC could be completed by PBS. Coho % population is only a rough estimate , abundance estimates aren't strictly defensible. Extreme low water early and mid. Fall. Periods of time when streambed was dry well into November. Gravel build up continues and in some area (lower section 1) is above level of streambed. Survey on Oct. 30th was done by the coho survey crew (Laurence Box and Jack Newman) - this survey was added to the BC16 by Brenda Wright (StAD) in Nov. 2001. Surveyors observed 20 coho.
